XRD analysis is used to determine the crystalline properties of NPs. In this work, XRD analysis of CuO NPs obtained by green synthesis is shown in Fig. 4a. Small different diffraction peaks at 32.80, 39.75, 61.40 and 71.02, that indexed the planes 111, 200, 220 and 311 of face centered cubic structure of CuO NPs with a monoclinic phase (JCPDS- 87-0717). CuO NPs synthesized from B. ciliata rhizome extract have been shown to be crystalline in nature by XRD analysis and no other phase shows that the purity of these NPs has been observed. The Debye-Scherrer equation was used to measure the crystal size of the NPs obtained [26]:
